<ul><li>Individual modules can be&nbsp;<u>separately tested</u>.</li><li>Modules can be kept in a&nbsp;<i>library</i>&nbsp;and be&nbsp;<u>reused in other programs</u>.</li><li>Large programs can be split into modules that are&nbsp;<b>easier to read, debug and maintain</b>.</li><li>Several programmers can&nbsp;<u>work on separate modules</u>, speeding up development time.</li></ul>